mods.abstract: The California Magazine of Western Square and Round Dancing by the Square Dancers of Southern California. This edition includes a table of contents which lists the following: "From the Floor", "Square Dance Date Book", "On the Record and Record Report", "As I See It", "The Hoedown Caper", "Favorite Square Dance Christmas Gift", "Overseas Dateline", "The Dancer's Walkthru", "A Husband and Wife Partnership in Teaching Squares and Rounds", "Why Doesn't Somebody - ?", "Real "Callenge" Dancing", "Everybody Travels on The Thru-Way", "Square Dancing - A Useful Therapy", "Style Series: Half Promenade and Promenade Half", "Round the Outside Ring", "Caller of the Month: Bob Dawson", "Paging the Roundancers: Aubrey and Peggy Tuttlebee", and "Experimental Lab: Fold a Girl - Fold a Boy".
